 add a tutorial table of contents file to your documentation catalog. Ensure the filename ends with ","type":"text"},{"code":".tutorial","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then copy and paste the template below into your editor. Replace the placeholder content provided with custom content.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"wrap":100,"highlight":[],"syntax":"markdown","code":["@Tutorials(name: \"SlothCreator\") {","    @Intro(title: \"Meet SlothCreator\") {","        Create, catalog, and care for sloths using SlothCreator. ","        Get started with SlothCreator by building the demo app _Slothy_.","        ","        @Image(source: slothcreator-intro, alt: \"An illustration of 3 iPhones in portrait mode, displaying the UI of finding, creating, and taking care of a sloth in Slothy — the sample app that you build in this collection of tutorials.\")","    }","    ","    @Chapter(name: \"SlothCreator Essentials\") {","        @Image(source: chapter1-slothcreatorEssentials, alt: \"A wireframe of an app interface that has an outline of a sloth and four buttons below the sloth. The buttons display the following symbols, from left to right: snowflake, fire, wind, and lightning.\")","        ","        Create custom sloths and edit their attributes and powers using SlothCreator.","        ","        @TutorialReference(tutorial: \"doc:Creating-Custom-Sloths\")","    }","}"],"copyToClipboard":true,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter to specify the name of your overall tutorial. This appears throughout the tutorial and in the tutorial’s URL when published on the web. Next, use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/Intro","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directive to introduce the reader to your tutorial through engaging text and imagery. Then, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/Chapter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directives to reference the step-by-step pages. Chapters can also include images."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Group Related Chapters","level":3,"anchor":"Group-Related-Chapters","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/Volume"},{"type":"text","text":" directive to group related chapters together if you need another level of organization. Volumes can also include images."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"wrap":100,"highlight":[],"syntax":"markdown","code":["@Tutorials(name: \"SlothCreator\") {","    @Intro(title: \"Meet SlothCreator\") {","        ","        ...","    }","    ","    @Volume(name: \"Getting Started\") {","        Building sloths, caring for them, and interacting with them.","        ","        @Chapter(name: \"SlothCreator Essentials\") {","            ...","        }","        ","        @Chapter(name: \"Basic Sloth Care\") {","            ...","        }","        ","        @Chapter(name: \"Basic Sloth Interaction\") {","            ...","        }","    }","    ","    @Volume(name: \"Climbing Higher\") {","        Taking your sloths to the next level.","        ","        @Chapter(name: \"Powering Up\") {","            ...","        }","    ","        ...","    }","    ","   ...","}"],"copyToClipboard":true,"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Offer Resources for Continued Learning","level":3,"anchor":"Offer-Resources-for-Continued-Learning","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your tutorial has related resources, use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/Resources","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directive to share them."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"wrap":100,"highlight":[],"syntax":"markdown","code":["@Tutorials(name: \"SlothCreator\") {","    @Intro(title: \"Meet SlothCreator\") {","        ","  